It’s been a rewarding journey sharing the visuals I created for the MOLOTOW brush pack. 🙌

Every render was built entirely in—with all assets modeled by hand using photo references for textures.
I focused on modeling primarily for the camera angle, leaving just enough geometry to tweak things when needed so I could optimize my time spent on the whole project while keeping the visual standard I strive for. 💪

Balancing multiple creative passion projects keeps my process fresh and helps me avoid burnout—and this project is no exception. It’s all about finding that sweet spot between maximum effort where it counts and smart optimizations that keep the workflow efficient.

I’m excited to share more about this project that not only reflects my love for graffiti but also demonstrates the creative and technical decisions that drive great visuals. 🫶